                                 expenv

Expenv is an awk script that expands environment variables from a text.
Expenv evaluates shell expressions (such ${var} or $var), reading from
a file or stdin.


ยง Usage

	$ expenv < inputfile > outputfile


ยง Example input

	My PWD is $PWD
	Whoami: ${USER}
	I'm using $TERM


ยง See also

For a Go and a Shell implementation of expenv, checkout [1] and [2].

[1]: https://github.com/blang/expenv
[2]: https://github.com/blang/expenv.sh


